---
name: PR Changelog Authoring
description: >-
  Ensures each pull request either contains a valid ## Changelog section in its body or
  explicitly opts out with the no-changelog label. Triggered after Build/Lint/Test completes.
  Deterministic pre-activation steps resolve the PR, check the no-changelog label, and
  validate any existing changelog section. The agent only drafts a missing section from
  PR title and description.
on:
  workflow_run:
    workflows: ["Build/Lint/Test"]
    types: [completed]
  steps:
    - name: Check for pull-request event
      id: check_pr_event
      uses: actions/github-script@v8
      with:
        github-token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
        script: |
          const eventName = context.payload.workflow_run?.event;
          const isPR = eventName === 'pull_request';
          core.info(`Triggering workflow_run event: ${eventName}`);
          core.setOutput('is_pr_event', isPR ? 'true' : 'false');
          if (!isPR) {
            core.info(`Skipping: workflow_run was triggered by event '${eventName}', not 'pull_request'`);
          }
    - name: Resolve pull request
      id: resolve_pr
      if: steps.check_pr_event.outputs.is_pr_event == 'true'
      uses: actions/github-script@v8
      with:
        github-token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
        x-script-include: scripts/resolve-pr.inline.js
    - name: Validate or skip changelog section
      id: validate_changelog
      if: >-
        steps.resolve_pr.outputs.is_pr_event == 'true' &&
        steps.resolve_pr.outputs.has_no_changelog_label != 'true'
      uses: actions/github-script@v8
      env:
        PR_BODY: ${{ steps.resolve_pr.outputs.pr_body }}
        PR_NUMBER: ${{ steps.resolve_pr.outputs.pr_number }}
      with:
        github-token: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}
        x-script-include: scripts/validate-pr-changelog.inline.js
steps:
  - name: Setup Node.js
    uses: actions/setup-node@v6
    with:
      node-version-file: package.json
engine:
  id: claude
  model: "llm-gateway/gpt-5.4"
  env:
    ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL: "https://elastic.litellm-prod.ai"
    ANTHROPIC_API_KEY: ${{ secrets.CLAUDE_LITELLM_PROXY_API_KEY }}
permissions:
  contents: read
  pull-requests: write
jobs:
  pre_activation:
    outputs:
      is_pr_event: ${{ steps.resolve_pr.outputs.is_pr_event }}
      pr_number: ${{ steps.resolve_pr.outputs.pr_number }}
      pr_title: ${{ steps.resolve_pr.outputs.pr_title }}
      pr_body: ${{ steps.resolve_pr.outputs.pr_body }}
      pr_url: ${{ steps.resolve_pr.outputs.pr_url }}
      has_no_changelog_label: ${{ steps.resolve_pr.outputs.has_no_changelog_label }}
      changelog_present: ${{ steps.validate_changelog.outputs.changelog_present }}
      changelog_valid: ${{ steps.validate_changelog.outputs.changelog_valid }}
if: >-
  needs.pre_activation.outputs.is_pr_event == 'true' &&
  needs.pre_activation.outputs.changelog_present == 'false'
tools:
  github:
    toolsets: [pull_requests]
network:
  allowed: [defaults, node, elastic.litellm-prod.ai]
safe-outputs:
  update-pull-request:
    max: 1
  noop:
    max: 1
    report-as-issue: false
---

# PR Changelog Authoring

You draft a missing `## Changelog` section for a pull request. You operate strictly from the pull-request metadata provided below — you do **not** check out or execute any code from the pull-request branch.

## Pre-activation context

Deterministic pre-activation steps have already resolved the pull request and confirmed it needs a `## Changelog` section. Do **not** re-query GitHub for PR metadata; use the values below.

- **PR number**: `${{ needs.pre_activation.outputs.pr_number }}`
- **PR title**: `${{ needs.pre_activation.outputs.pr_title }}`
- **PR URL**: `${{ needs.pre_activation.outputs.pr_url }}`

The existing PR body (which does **not** contain a `## Changelog` section):

```
${{ needs.pre_activation.outputs.pr_body }}
```

## Your task

1. **Read the PR title and description** above to understand the change.

2. **Draft the `## Changelog` section** using this exact template:

   ```markdown
   ## Changelog
   Customer impact: <none|fix|enhancement|breaking>
   Summary: <one-line user-facing description>
   ```

   Field rules:
   - `Customer impact` MUST be exactly one of: `none`, `fix`, `enhancement`, `breaking` (case-sensitive, no other values).
   - `Summary` is required when `Customer impact` is not `none`. It should be a concise, user-facing one-line description of the change.
   - If `Customer impact` is `none`, omit the `Summary` line entirely.
   - If `Customer impact` is `breaking`, append a `### Breaking changes` subsection with a brief description of the breaking change and any migration notes. Free-form markdown is allowed (prose, bullets, fenced code).

3. **Choose `Customer impact` carefully**:
   - `none`: purely internal, CI, documentation, or test-only changes with no effect on provider users.
   - `fix`: a bug fix that resolves incorrect provider behavior.
   - `enhancement`: a new feature, new resource, new data source, or improvement to existing functionality.
   - `breaking`: a change that requires users to update their Terraform configurations or state.

4. **Append the drafted section** to the existing PR body. Place `## Changelog` at the end of the body, separated from the preceding content by a blank line. Do **not** replace or remove any existing PR body content — only append.

5. **Update the PR body** using the `update_pull_request` safe output with the updated body text.

## Constraints

- Do **not** check out or execute code from the PR branch. Operate only on the metadata above.
- Do **not** overwrite or remove any existing content in the PR body.
- Do **not** invent technical details not supported by the PR title and description.
- When in doubt about customer impact, prefer `fix` or `enhancement` over `none`.
- If the PR title and description provide no useful signal for drafting a summary, use the PR title as the summary.
- If you cannot determine the appropriate changelog section from the available metadata, emit `noop` with a clear explanation instead of guessing or writing an empty section.
